         <div type="edition">
            <note>The order of the miracles is in correspondance to <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>. The labels
               are taken from <bibl><ptr target="bm:Strelcyn1976Catalogue"/><citedRange unit="page">210–216</citedRange></bibl>.</note>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle1">
               <label>The miraculous infancy of Zarʾa Buruk</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 1 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle2">
               <label>The miracle of the Queen’s visit and the new king’s persecution</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 2 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle3">
               <label>The miracle of Zarʾa Buruk’s imprisonment</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 3 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle4">
               <label>How Zarʾa Buruk gained entry to the Kingdom of Heaven while still alive</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 4 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle5">
               <label>How Zarʾa Buruk was welcomed into Heavenly Jerusalem</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 5 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle6">
               <label>How Zarʾa Buruk, the second Peter, obtains the keys to the Heavenly Kingdom</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 6 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle7">
               <label>How Zarʾa Buruk liberates damned souls from hell</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 7 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle8">
               <label>How Zarʾa Buruk frees ʾAbsādi, disciple of Ewosṭātewos, from hell</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 8 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle9">
               <label>How the greatness of Zarʾa Buruk is recognised by the most eminent Ethiopian saints</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 9 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle10">
               <label>After Zarʾa Buruk’s leg broke while he was standing and praying, God gave him a spiritual leg.</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 10 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle11">
               <label>How John, Patriarch of Alexandria, recognised Zarʾa Buruk</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 11 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle12">
               <label>How Zarʾa Buruk promised redemption to those who worship him</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 12 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle13">
               <label>The duties of those who worship Zarʾa Buruk, and the rewards awaiting them</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 13 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle14">
               <label>The resurrection of a dead woman</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 14 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle15">
               <label>Healing of an ill woman at the tomb of Zarʾa Buruk</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 15 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle16">
               <label>The punishment of the man who denounced to the governor the inhabitants of a town who worshipped Zarʾa Buruk</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 16 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle17">
               <label>The miraculous cross of Zarʾa Buruk</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 17 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle18">
               <label>The mystery of baptism: Benediction by the saint of the waters on Epiphany Day and miracles performed thanks to the
                  water blessed by him</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 18 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle19">
               <label>Zarʾa Buruk receives instructions form God to banish tobacco</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 19 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle20">
               <label>Zarʾa Buruk receives the pact giving him power next to that of God</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 20 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle21">
               <label>Zarʾa Buruk receives the pact as the saviour of the world</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 21 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle22">
               <label>The mystery of the three pearls</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 22 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle23">
               <label>New distinction of Zarʾa Buruk and promises made to those who venerate him</label>
               <note>This miracle was numbered 23 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle24">
               <label>Miracles after the death of Zarʾa Buruk</label>
               <note>These miracles were numbered 25 in <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle25">
               <label>The healing of children bitten by a rabid dog</label>
               <note>This miracle is attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr83"/>, but not in
                  <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle26">
               <label>Miracle accomplished at Dabra Sān thanks to the intercession of Zarʾa Buruk</label>
               <note>This miracle is attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr83"/>, but not in
                  <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle27">
               <label>The healing of a woman with syphilis</label>
               <note>This miracle is attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr83"/>, but not in
                  <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="textpart" xml:id="Miracle28">
               <label>Miracles performed on the day of Zarʾa Buruk’s death</label>
               <note>This miracle is attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="ANLcr83"/>, but not in
                  <bibl><ptr target="bm:Jaeger1912ZaraBuruk"/></bibl>.</note>
            </div>
         </div>            
